22 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 51.1b of Title 74, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 12641 Page 1

1 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Targeted
2 Violence Prevention Act".
3 B. In furtherance of its core functions of prevention and
4 intelligence, response and recovery planning, and awareness and
5 preparedness, the Office of Homeland Security and the Oklahoma
6 Counter Terrorism Intelligence Center, a unit of the Office of
7 Homeland Security, may collect, analyze, and disseminate to law
8 enforcement and public safety agencies information concerning the
9 activity and identity of individuals reasonably suspected of
10 involvement in terrorism, targeted violence, threats to public
11 safety, or any other threats of organized or violent crime.
12 C. Any information disseminated pursuant to this section shall
13 be confidential and the recipients of such information shall comply
14 with the handling terms associated with the disclosure.
15 Unauthorized release or unauthorized use of information disseminated
16 pursuant to this section shall be a misdemeanor and shall be
17 punishable by incarceration in the county jail for a term not
18 exceeding one (1) year, or a fine not exceeding Fifty Thousand
19 Dollars ($50,000.00), or by both such fine and imprisonment. As
20 used in this subsection, "unauthorized release" or "unauthorized
21 use" shall include, but not be limited to, disseminating or
22 disclosing confidential information in a manner which exceeds the
23 scope of the handling terms associated with the disclosure or in
24 violation of any rules promulgated pursuant to the authority of this
Req. No. 12641 Page 2

1 act. Provided, the following shall not constitute an unauthorized
2 release or unauthorized use of confidential information disseminated
3 pursuant to this section:
4 1. Sharing the confidential information with a law enforcement
5 officer or prosecutorial authority for use in a criminal
6 investigation or prosecution;
7 2. Sharing the confidential information, in exigent
8 circumstances, with leadership of the State or any political
